<div class="row" style="font-size:larger">
    Looking for the Microsoft Starter Kit information with links to info and tutorials? <br />
    In this Manukau-Tech-customised starter kit, we have moved it to the
    <a href="~/Home/About">"About Page"</a><br />
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Info about ASP.NET Core 2.0 Layout</h2>
        <p>
            Here we see a 3-column "responsive" layout using the very
            common and popular css library file "bootstrap.css".
            The code keywords used here are 'class="row"' for the parent
            div of this this row of 3 text blocks<br />
            and 'class="col-md-4"' for the 3 child div elements which are
            the containers of these text blocks. Now we can investigate
            why a 3 column layout has a class with "4" in its name.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Block Number 2</h2>
        <p>
            Second block of text in this demonstration series
            of 3 responsive columns using "bootstrap.css".
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Block Number 3</h2>
        <p>
            Third block of text in this demonstration series
            of 3 responsive columns using "bootstrap.css".
            "bootstrap.css" was developed by "Twitter" who have
            made it available free to anyone interested. It is
            now very popular which has had the effect of making
            lots of websites look like "Twitter". Please dear students
            override some of these classes to give us some variety!
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
